  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "1.1 Preparation of a national strategic action plan on eradication of child labour in agriculture1.2 Conduct consultations meetings at various level and a national validation workshop2.1 Launch the first national dialogue meeting focusing on agriculture2.2 Organize regular coordination meetings with the stakeholders at federal, provincial, and local level2.3 Conduct an assessment on the stakeholders needs and existing systems including gaps and opportunities2.4 Organization of the monitoring visits in the piloted municipalities3.1 Organize ToT to build capacity of the extension workers on OSH and exposure to hazards, and hazardous pesticides3.2 Organize training to the municipality based professional staff3.3 Adopting Municipality piloting cases with the enhanced visual tool3.4   Participate in the national level conference on Child labour, forced labor and Human Trafficking3.5 Develop IEC materials (printed materials, newspaper articles,) success stories to launch through a mass media campaign for raising awareness3.6 Organize result sharing meeting"
    },
    "ne": null
